  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there were-- these doctors, many of them, were distinguished German scientists, doctors.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Dr.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Rose, in particular, I remember.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] In universities, clinics, hospitals, all throughout Germany, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] charged with-- with these crimes.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] they were charged with 12 major experiments.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "There were actually 14, but the final two were incorporated, really, into the other major-- these 12 major that I-- that I reported and talk about.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] With the outright murder of political prisoners, non-German nationals, intellectual dissidents, intellectual German dissidents, Catholic and Protestant clergy, and prisoners of war, especially Russian prisoners of war, through medical experimentation.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Those who did not die or who were not deliberately murdered just suffered torture and maiming and permanent disfigurement and disability.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They were ordered in wholesale lots.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I remember the orders being-- especially had I become so aware of the anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] 200 Jews in good physical condition would be the order. 50 gypsies, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] 500 tubercular Poles, 1,000 Russian prisoners of war.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And the first experiment that they were charged with was high altitude, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] which was conducted at Dachau [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] in-- in the summer of 1942.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I thought at that time, that was the summer I graduated from high school.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And this experiment was conducted to determine or study the limits of human existence and endurance at extremely high altitudes, up to 68,000 feet, without oxygen.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And the victims were placed in airtight, ball-shaped compartments, and then high altitude atmospheric conditions were simulated by the alteration of pressure.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Up to 68,000 feet, without oxygen.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
